<NOTE>Weicker To Head New Group To Promote Medical Research</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lowell P. Weicker Jr. will be the chief of a
new non-profit organization devoted to increasing government funding
for medical research, a field that became a speciality for the
Connecticut Republican during his 18-year Senate career.
   Weicker, who lost a bid for a fourth Senate term in November,
will become president and chief executive officer of ``Research!
America,'' which will open in Alexandria, Va., this spring,
publicist Jane Miller said Thursday.
