<HEAD>Six Climbers Die In Soviet Avalanche</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An avalanche on a mountain in Soviet Central Asia
roared down on six climbers, burying and killing them, a newspaper
said.
   The paper, Komsomolskaya Pravda, said the climbers had ignored
avalanche warnings in the earthquake-prone area of the Pamir
mountains in Tadjikistan republic.
   In its report Thursday, the newspaper said the accident happened
recently but gave no date.
   The team of six had been hauling equipment to an intermediary
camp at 18,000 feet, the report said. It was returning to the main
camp at 12,000 feet when the avalanche occurred.
   Only one body was recovered, the newspaper added.
