<SECOND>PM-Finland-Plane,0111</SECOND>
<HEAD>Seven Killed In Crash Of Light Plane</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HELSINKI, Finland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A twin-engine plane crashed at the end
of a runway while trying to land, killing seven of the eight Finns
on board, aviation officials said today.
   The lone survivor of the crash at Helsinki's international
airport suffered minor injuries and walked 400 yards from the crash
site before rescue teams reached her, officials said.
   The Fairchild Metro aircraft went down around midnight Thursday
in light fog, they said. The plane was returning to Finland from
Southend, England.
   No cause of the crash was immediately given. The government today
appointed a special committee to investigate.
