<HEAD>Tyson Says His Sense Of Humor Is From Brooklyn</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Heavyweight champ Mike Tyson says he credits his
sense of humor, picked up on the streets of Brooklyn, for helping
him through a year of seemingly unceasing media scrutiny of his
private life.
   ``That Brooklyn sense of humor _ that's like no other place in
the world,'' Tyson said in an interview in today's New York Post.
``If I took all that stuff as serious as it appeared, man, I really
would be manic.''
   Tyson, who will defend his title against Frank Bruno in Las Vegas
Saturday, says he occasionally visits his old Brownsville
neighborhood, ``but since crack nothing's the same, nothing good's
happening, my old friends are gone or dead or worse.
   ``I see these guys on crack, like zombies, no will, no spirit.
Something's got to be done about that ... but it would be
un-Christian to say what I think should be done.''
