<SECOND>PM-Juror Arrested,0348</SECOND>
<HEAD>Juror in Drug-Related Trial Arrested on Cocaine Charge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BALTIMORE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 23-year-old man serving as a juror in a
drug-related murder trial was arrested on charges he tried to enter
the downtown courthouse carrying a hidden bag of cocaine.
   Gary M. Lewis of Baltimore was arrested upon his return from a
lunch break when a metal detector went off and authorities found a
zippered pouch containing the drugs inside his coat.
   ``It just goes to show you that it is possible to get a jury of
your peers,'' a court official said.
   Lewis was charged with possession of cocaine and possession of
cocaine with intent to distribute, authorities said.
   Lewis was a juror in the first-degree murder trial of Lucien C.
Derbigney, who is accused of killing a 66-year-old man during what
prosecutors described as a narcotics dispute last September.
   According to Leonard Santivasci, a deputy chief in the sheriff's
office, Lewis returned to the courthouse carrying a bag from a
fast-food restaurant and when he entered the Clarence M. Mitchell
Jr. Courthouse, a metal detector alarm sounded.
   A deputy told Lewis to empty his pockets and sent him back
through the detector, but the alarm went off again.
   The deputy used a hand-held scanner to check Lewis and found a
brown leather pouch stashed in his inside coat pocket, allegedly
containing cocaine with a street value of about $750, police said.
   Apparently, the pouch's metal zipper and two cigarette lighters
activated the metal detector, authorities said.
   ``He made no statement. All I said to him was: `Is this coke?'
And he said, `Yeah,''' said Santivasci.
   Lewis was dismissed from the jury, and Judge Elsbeth Levy Bothe,
who is presiding over the trial, told him not to discuss the case
with anyone at the jail.
   It was the second time in three months that drugs were
confiscated from someone entering the courthouse.
   On Nov. 21, Jerome Kesler, 19, was charged with possession of
heroin and possession of heroin with intent to distribute.
</TEXT>
