<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``The people will remember him forever.'' _ Emperor Akihito,
eulogizing Emperor Hirohito at the funeral of the late Japanese
monarch, who was worshiped as a living god and branded a war
criminal during his long life.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``It's simply one more bad effect of cigarette smoking _ as if
you needed one more bad effect.'' _ Dr. Reubin Andres, co-author of
a study in the Journal of the American Medical Association that
found people who smoke to control their weight are simply
redistributing their fat in unhealthy ways.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``They're about as smart as a damned old milk cow.'' _ Ellery
Merrell, a 73-year-old Montana rancher, on bison and the fate of
about 500 buffalo that likely will die when they're declared fair
game on Monday.
</TEXT>
