<FIRST>r i PM-BuddhaArrests 2ndLd-Writethru   02-24 0190</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Buddha Arrests, 2nd Ld-Writethru,a0522,0192</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Americans Accused Of Desecrating Statue</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Recasts lede, edits throughout to tighten.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An American photographer and an American
model who posed in her underwear while sitting on a Buddha statue
were arrested on charges of desecrating the statue, police said
today.
   Sante Maria D'Razzio, 33, of New Jersey and Kara Ruth Young, 23,
of California were arrested Sunday after the photo session inside
Chung Len Buddhist temple in the southern island resort of Phuket,
said police Lt. Amnuey Kraiwuttianant said. Hometowns for the two
were not immediately known.
   D'Razzio was photographing Ms. Young for the French magazine
Vogue when worshipers at the temple complained to police, Amnuey
said.
   When authorities arrived, they found Ms. Young sitting in a car
in her underwear, and they seized an instant photograph taken of her
sitting on the statue, the officer said.
   The pair said they did not know they were breaking the law,
Amnuey said. Thailand is a predominately Buddhist country.
   They each could face a maximum sentence of seven years in prison
if convicted. They were released on $2,000 bail each.
</TEXT>
