<TEXT>
   A truck plunged into a flooded river in
mountainous eastern Zimbabwe, and seven road department employees
were feared drowned, police said Friday.
   Four bodies were recovered from the swollen Murozi River and
authorities were searching for three other men missing since the
truck plunged off a bridge into the river Wednesday, a police
