<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Indonesia-Flood     02-24 0118</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Indonesia-Flood,0121</SECOND>
<HEAD>Three Killed In Floods, 15,000 Left Homeless</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Heavy rains caused floods that have
left three people dead and about 15,000 homeless in central Java, a
government official said Friday.
   The three drowned when the Muarareja River in central Java
overflowed Wednesday, said an official of the Social Affairs
Ministry.
   Thirty others have been treated for injuries and about 15,000
people forced to evacuate homes in the districts of Tegal and
Brebes, said the official on condition of anonymity. The districts
are 310 miles southeast of Jakarta.
   Floodwaters began receding Friday, ``but the evacuees have yet to
wait for a few more days before they can return to their villages,''
he said.
