<FIRST>r a RecordLottoAmericaJackpotStillUnclaimed     02-24 0193</FIRST>
<SECOND>Record Lotto America Jackpot Still Unclaimed</SECOND>
<DATELINE>DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nearly a week after the number for a $16
million lottery was picked, the winner of the multi-state contest's
largest jackpot is still unknown.
   The winning ticket for Lotto America's $16 million prize was sold
at a convenience store in the District of Columbia, but no one has
claimed the money, game spokesman Charles Strutt said Friday.
   The ticket was picked in a Feb. 18 drawing.
   This is the first time that anyone outside of Iowa or Kansas has
won the lottery game, which began about a year ago. The game's
previous record jackpot, $13.6 million, was claimed by a Norwalk,
Iowa, couple last December.
   The winner has one year from the date of the drawing to claim the
prize, Strutt said. If the $16 million remains unclaimed, it is
divided among the states in the Lotto America game, according to the
percentage of sales in each place for that jackpot, Strutt said.
   The other states in the Lotto America game are Missouri, Oregon,
West Virginia and Rhode Island.
   The winning numbers were 9, 17, 20, 28, 46 and 50.
</TEXT>
