<FIRST>r a AM-People-Weicker     02-24 0222</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-Weicker,0228</SECOND>
<HEAD>Weicker To Head New Group To Promote Medical Research</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Research! America is cq</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Sen. Lowell P. Weicker Jr. will be the
chief of a new non-profit organization devoted to increasing
government funding for medical research.
   The Connecticut Republican, who lost his bid for a fourth Senate
term in November, will become president and chief executive officer
of Research! America, which will open its doors in Alexandria, Va.,
this spring, publicist Jane Miller said Thursday.
   Weicker would not discuss details of the new organization.
   Terry Lierman, a Washington lobbyist who founded the group, said
the organization plans to spend about $3 million a year on an
education campaign that will feature Weicker speaking around the
country.
   Weicker was a leader for medical research, especially for AIDS
and the handicapped, throughout his Capitol Hill career. One of his
sons, Sonny, suffers from Down's syndrome.
   ``He was Mr. Research in the United States Senate, so he brings a
tremendous amount of prestige and credit to the organization
immediately,'' said Lierman, president of Capitol Associates Inc.
   Lierman said Research! America will act as an umbrella group for
a wide range of academic, fund-raising, industry and research
groups, including the National Multiple Sclerosis Society, Cystic
Fibrosis Foundation, American Association of Universities, American
Association of Medical Colleges and Upjohn Co.
