<HEAD>Fixed-rate Mortgages Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fixed-rate home mortgages are averaging 10.78
percent, according to a national survey released Friday by the
Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp.
   That rate was up from a rate of 10.69 percent last week.
   On one-year adjustable rate mortgages, lenders were asking an
average initial rate of 8.73 percent this week, up from 8.68 percent
the week before, Freddie Mac said.
