<FIRST>r f AM-Coastal-TexasEastern     02-24 0238</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Coastal-Texas Eastern,0247</SECOND>
<HEAD>Coastal Extends Offer For Texas Eastern Stock</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Coastal Corp., stalling for time to consider what
to do next in its quest to buy Texas Eastern Corp., said Friday it
had extended its $2.6 billion offer for the natural gas company.
   Coastal spokesman Jim Bailey said Coastal extended its
$42-a-share offer, which had expired at midnight Thursday, until
March 10.
   ``What this extension does is preserve our options. It gives us
time to review the courses of action that are available to us, which
include raising the offer,'' Bailey said.
   Texas Eastern, which has rejected Coastal's hostile takeover
offer, on Monday accepted a $3.2 billion, $53-a-share, offer to
merge with Panhandle Eastern. All three natural gas companies are
based in Houston.
   Since Coastal launched its tender offer on Jan. 17, Texas Eastern
stock has soared, closing at $52.25 on the New York Stock Exchange,
unchanged from Thursday's close.
   Panhandle Eastern began a cash tender offer Tuesday for up to 80
percent of Texas Eastern's 60.8 million outstanding shares at $53 a
share. Those shares not purchased under the cash offer will be
exchanged for Panhandle Eastern stock at the same $53 a share.
   Panhandle's offer expires March 20.
   If the merger is completed, the combination of Panhandle Eastern
and Texas Eastern would create a 27,000-mile pipeline system and
produce the nation's second-largest pipeline company in total miles,
Panhandle Eastern officials have said.
</TEXT>
